All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    Author
    Represents authors who write books for a living.
    Band
    Represent a band, which is comprised of a collection of RecordingArtists.
    Book
    Represents a book item, which retains an author as its creator, as well as its title and the year it was published.
    Catalog
    Represents a catalog retaining written and audio works (books and music), created by associated authors, individual recording artists and bands, alike.
    Creator  
    Donation
    Represents donations made to non-profit organizations, according to their date of donation/pledge as well as the amount given/promised.
    ICatalog
    Provides the functionality of a catalog retaining a library of music and books generated by a variety of authors, individual recording artists and bands.
    IDonation
    Provides the functionality utilized by Donations, including their calculation.
    IEndDate
    Interface providing the ability to check the validity of submitted ending dates (cancellation and processing dates) of donations, in relation to their creation.
    ImproperCreatorException
    Exception extension, which throws an exception when one attempts to establish an item with an unassociated creator.
    IndividualCreator
    Represents individuals that generate some form of content -- in this particular case, either books or music.
    INonProfit
    Provides the functionality afforded to NonProfits, including the ability to calculate all donations received (or to be received) within a certain year.
    InvalidDateException
    Exception extension, which throws an exception when one attempts to submit a date incompatible with the context in which it is used.
    Item
    Represents the two possible items that may be stored within a catalog -- books and music.
    MonthlyDonation
    Represents a monthly donation subscription, which bills the donor an established amount at the same time of day each month, until the end of the subscription is reached.
    Music  
    NonProfit
    Represents non-profit organizations, recording all donations made to them and reporting their yearly gains.
    OneTimeDonation
    Represents donations to non-profit organizations that are only made once (without subscription).
    Pledge
    Represents a pledge made to donate a sum of money to a non-profit organization at a specified point in time.
    RecordingArtist
    Represents recording artists who create music for a living.
    UnacceptableLibraryException
    Exception extension, which throws an exception when one attempts to initialize a Catalog object with a null reference in place of a library.
